06/10/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Civil servants and government officials announced on Tuesday (October 5th) plans for a 24-hour strike Thursday against austerity measures introduced by the government. 
The action will affect government buildings, schools and airports. 
Dozens of flights are expected to be cancelled amid a planned 4-hour closure of Greek airspace, starting at 2pm local time Thursday. 
(DPA, Reuters, ANA-MPA - 05/10/10)
